It is the holiest city for Hindus. It is the Avimukta Kshetra where Purusha and Prakriti dwelt first. Varanasi is Shiva KShetra. It was a Vishnu KShetra before. \r\n Varanasi is settle next to the left banks of the Ganga and numerous Ghats line up their. Varanasi is also the dwelling place of Shiva where he lives as the Vishweshwar Linga in the Kashi Viswanath Mandir at Gyanvapi.\r\n \n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nThe Assi River\nThe Assi River flows into the Ganga at the famous Assi Ghat. The Assi Ghat is famous as the dwelling place of Goswami Tulsidas ji.\r\n The Ramacharita Manas was composed here. The Assi Ghat is famous for the early morning Kirtans and cultural activities. The Ganga Aarti takes place here.\r\n The Assi River flows next to the Baba Kinarama Asthal. The river has unfortunately been polluted beyond recognition by sewers emptying into it.\r\n Efforts are being made to revive it.\r\n \n\n\n\n\n\n\nPlaces in Varanasi\n\n\n\n\nBheem Chandi\nBheem Chandi,Rameshwar\n\n\n\n\n\nRameshwar Mahadev Mandir on the Varuna\nThird stop on the Panchkoshi parikrama\n\n\n\n\n\nKapil Dhara, Varanasi\nLast stop on the Panchkoshi parikrama Yatra\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nBhairav Nath Mandir.\nOn the Rajatalab to Jansa Road\n\n\n\n\n\nPancha Pandava Mandir, Varanasi\n fourth stop on the Kashi Panchkoshi parikrama.\n\n\n\n\n\nKapil Dhara, Varanasi\nFifth and last stop on the Panchkoshi parikrama\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nMap of Varanasi\n\n\n\n\n\n\n NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN

Varanasi is also the dwelling place of Shiva where he lives as the Vishweshwar Linga in the Kashi Viswanath Mandir at Gyanvapi.\r\n \n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nThe Assi River\nThe Assi River flows into the Ganga at the famous Assi Ghat. The Assi Ghat is famous as the dwelling place of Goswami Tulsidas ji.\r\n The Ramacharita Manas was composed here. The Assi Ghat is famous for the early morning Kirtans and cultural activities. The Ganga Aarti takes place here.\r\n The Assi River flows next to the Baba Kinarama Asthal. The river has unfortunately been polluted beyond recognition by sewers emptying into it.\r\n Efforts are being made to revive it.\r\n \n\n\n\n\n\n\nPlaces in Varanasi\n\n\n\n\nBheem Chandi\nBheem Chandi,Rameshwar\n\n\n\n\n\nRameshwar Mahadev Mandir on the Varuna\nThird stop on the Panchkoshi parikrama\n\n\n\n\n\nKapil Dhara, Varanasi\nLast stop on the Panchkoshi parikrama Yatra\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nBhairav Nath Mandir.\nOn the Rajatalab to Jansa Road\n\n\n\n\n\nPancha Pandava Mandir, Varanasi\n fourth stop on the Kashi Panchkoshi parikrama.\n\n\n\n\n\nKapil Dhara, Varanasi\nFifth and last stop on the Panchkoshi parikrama\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nMap of Varanasi\n\n\n\n NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN

It is the holiest city for Hindus. It is the Avimukta Kshetra where Purusha and Prakriti dwelt first. Varanasi is Shiva KShetra. It was a Vishnu KShetra before. \r\n Varanasi is settle next to the left banks of the Ganga and numerous Ghats line up their. Varanasi is also the dwelling place of Shiva where he lives as the Vishweshwar Linga in the Kashi Viswanath Mandir at Gyanvapi.\r\n \n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nThe Assi River\nThe Assi River flows into the Ganga at the famous Assi Ghat. The Assi Ghat is famous as the dwelling place of Goswami Tulsidas ji.\r\n The Ramacharita Manas was composed here. The Assi Ghat is famous for the early morning Kirtans and cultural activities. The Ganga Aarti takes place here.\r\n The Assi River flows next to the Baba Kinarama Asthal. The river has unfortunately been polluted beyond recognition by sewers emptying into it.\r\n Efforts are being made to revive it.\r\n \n\n\n\n\n\n\nPlaces in Varanasi\n\n\n\n\nBheem Chandi\nBheem Chandi,Rameshwar\n\n\n\n\n\nRameshwar Mahadev Mandir on the Varuna\nThird stop on the Panchkoshi parikrama\n\n\n\n\n\nKapil Dhara, Varanasi\nLast stop on the Panchkoshi parikrama Yatra\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nBhairav Nath Mandir.\nOn the Rajatalab to Jansa Road\n\n\n\n\n\nPancha Pandava Mandir, Varanasi\n fourth stop on the Kashi Panchkoshi parikrama.\n\n\n\n\n\nKapil Dhara, Varanasi\nFifth and last stop on the Panchkoshi parikrama\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nMap of Varanasi\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nCONTACT\n\n\nContact us for any query about Varanasi and we'll get back to you within 24 hours.\n Varanasi, India\n +91 9335874326\n varanasikshetra@gmail.com\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nSend\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n©Champak's World\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n NaN NaN

0 \n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nDevi Bhim Chandi Mandir\nSecond stop on the Panch Koshi parikrama.\n\n\n\n\n\nView of the Ganga from Lalita Ghat\nBoats in the Ganga in Varanasi.\n\n\n\n\n\nApproach to Devi Bhim Chandi Mandir\nSecond stop on the Panch Koshi parikrama.\n\n\n\n\n\n\nPrevious\n\n\n\nNext\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nAbout Varanasi\nThe word Varanasi is made up of the two words Varuna and Assi.Varanasi is the city between the rivers Varuna and Assi. It is the holiest city for Hindus. It is the Avimukta Kshetra where Purusha and Prakriti dwelt first. Varanasi is Shiva KShetra. It was a Vishnu KShetra before. \r\n Varanasi is settle next to the left banks of the Ganga and numerous Ghats line up their. Varanasi is also the dwelling place of Shiva where he lives as the Vishweshwar Linga in the Kashi Viswanath Mandir at Gyanvapi.\r\n \n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nThe Assi River\nThe Assi River flows into the Ganga at the famous Assi Ghat. The Assi Ghat is famous as the dwelling place of Goswami Tulsidas ji.\r\n The Ramacharita Manas was composed here. The Assi Ghat is famous for the early morning Kirtans and cultural activities. The Ganga Aarti takes place here.\r\n The Assi River flows next to the Baba Kinarama Asthal. The river has unfortunately been polluted beyond recognition by sewers emptying into it.\r\n Efforts are being made to revive it.\r\n \n\n\n\n\n\n\nPlaces in Varanasi\n\n\n\n\nBheem Chandi\nBheem Chandi,Rameshwar\n\n\n\n\n\nRameshwar Mahadev Mandir on the Varuna\nThird stop on the Panchkoshi parikrama\n\n\n\n\n\nKapil Dhara, Varanasi\nLast stop on the Panchkoshi parikrama Yatra\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nBhairav Nath Mandir.\nOn the Rajatalab to Jansa Road\n\n\n\n\n\nPancha Pandava Mandir, Varanasi\n fourth stop on the Kashi Panchkoshi parikrama.\n\n\n\n\n\nKapil Dhara, Varanasi\nFifth and last stop on the Panchkoshi parikrama\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nMap of Varanasi\n\n\n\n\n\n\n NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN

2 NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN \n\nHome\n\nKashi Panchkoshi Parikrama \n\nKashi Panchkoshi Parikrama\nKardameshwar Mahadev\nBheem Chandi\nRameshwar Mahadev\nPanch Pandava\nKapil Dhara\n\n\n\nGalleries \n\nKardameshwar Mahadev\nBheem Chandi Gallery\nRameshwar Gallery\nKapil Dhara\n\n\n\nMandirs \n\nShri Adi Keshava Mandir\nMarkandeya Mahadev,Kaithi\nBhairav Nath Mandir\nDindaspur, Harsos, Jansa\nPahadia Mandir, Akhara and Sarovar\n\n\n\nGhats\nFestivals\n\n\n NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN
3 NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN \n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nDevi Bhim Chandi Mandir\nSecond stop on the Panch Koshi parikrama.\n\n\n\n\n\nView of the Ganga from Lalita Ghat\nBoats in the Ganga in Varanasi.\n\n\n\n\n\nApproach to Devi Bhim Chandi Mandir\nSecond stop on the Panch Koshi parikrama.\n\n\n\n\n\n\nPrevious\n\n\n\nNext\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nAbout Varanasi\nThe word Varanasi is made up of the two words Varuna and Assi.Varanasi is the city between the rivers Varuna and Assi. It is the holiest city for Hindus. It is the Avimukta Kshetra where Purusha and Prakriti dwelt first. Varanasi is Shiva KShetra. It was a Vishnu KShetra before. \r\n Varanasi is settle next to the left banks of the Ganga and numerous Ghats line up their. Varanasi is also the dwelling place of Shiva where he lives as the Vishweshwar Linga in the Kashi Viswanath Mandir at Gyanvapi.\r\n \n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nThe Assi River\nThe Assi River flows into the Ganga at the famous Assi Ghat. The Assi Ghat is famous as the dwelling place of Goswami Tulsidas ji.\r\n The Ramacharita Manas was composed here. The Assi Ghat is famous for the early morning Kirtans and cultural activities. The Ganga Aarti takes place here.\r\n The Assi River flows next to the Baba Kinarama Asthal. The river has unfortunately been polluted beyond recognition by sewers emptying into it.\r\n Efforts are being made to revive it.\r\n \n\n\n\n\n\n\nPlaces in Varanasi\n\n\n\n\nBheem Chandi\nBheem Chandi,Rameshwar\n\n\n\n\n\nRameshwar Mahadev Mandir on the Varuna\nThird stop on the Panchkoshi parikrama\n\n\n\n\n\nKapil Dhara, Varanasi\nLast stop on the Panchkoshi parikrama Yatra\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nBhairav Nath Mandir.\nOn the Rajatalab to Jansa Road\n\n\n\n\n\nPancha Pandava Mandir, Varanasi\n fourth stop on the Kashi Panchkoshi parikrama.\n\n\n\n\n\nKapil Dhara, Varanasi\nFifth and last stop on the Panchkoshi parikrama\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nMap of Varanasi\n\n\n\n\n\n NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN

It is the holiest city for Hindus. It is the Avimukta Kshetra where Purusha and Prakriti dwelt first. Varanasi is Shiva KShetra. It was a Vishnu KShetra before. \r\n Varanasi is settle next to the left banks of the Ganga and numerous Ghats line up their. Varanasi is also the dwelling place of Shiva where he lives as the Vishweshwar Linga in the Kashi Viswanath Mandir at Gyanvapi.\r\n \n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nThe Assi River\nThe Assi River flows into the Ganga at the famous Assi Ghat. The Assi Ghat is famous as the dwelling place of Goswami Tulsidas ji.\r\n The Ramacharita Manas was composed here. The Assi Ghat is famous for the early morning Kirtans and cultural activities. The Ganga Aarti takes place here.\r\n The Assi River flows next to the Baba Kinarama Asthal. The river has unfortunately been polluted beyond recognition by sewers emptying into it.\r\n Efforts are being made to revive it.\r\n \n\n\n\n\n\n\nPlaces in Varanasi\n\n\n\n\nBheem Chandi\nBheem Chandi,Rameshwar\n\n\n\n\n\nRameshwar Mahadev Mandir on the Varuna\nThird stop on the Panchkoshi parikrama\n\n\n\n\n\nKapil Dhara, Varanasi\nLast stop on the Panchkoshi parikrama Yatra\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nBhairav Nath Mandir.\nOn the Rajatalab to Jansa Road\n\n\n\n\n\nPancha Pandava Mandir, Varanasi\n fourth stop on the Kashi Panchkoshi parikrama.\n\n\n\n\n\nKapil Dhara, Varanasi\nFifth and last stop on the Panchkoshi parikrama\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nMap of Varanasi\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nCONTACT\n\n\nContact us for any query about Varanasi and we'll get back to you within 24 hours.\n Varanasi, India\n +91 9335874326\n varanasikshetra@gmail.com\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nSend\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n©Champak's World\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN

Even the Devas worship this land.\r\n The capital city of Tripurari Mahadev...\r\n \n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nThe Panchkoshi Kshetra\nThe Panchkoshi Kshetra in Varanasi is wonderfully endowed. The rivers Ganga, Varuna and Assi flow through the city. The Gomti flows nearby and joins the Ganga at Kaithi on the Varanasi-Ghazipur road. The Markandeya Mahadev Mandir is situated there.\r\n The Son river flows through nearby Sonebhadra. That apart there are inumerable kunds, sarovars all through the area.\r\n Innumerable Mandirs are found in the area.Kashi Viswanath, Bindu Madhava, Adi Keshava, Shool Tankeshwar, Mahakal,etc\r\n\r\n \n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nAbout the Panchkoshi Parikrama \n\r\n The Panchkoshi Kshetra in Varanasi is described in the Skanda Purana in these words:\r\n "Though it is on the earth, it has no contact with it.\r\n Being higher than the heavens, yet it is established on the earth.\r\n Even though it is made of the five elements it gives Moksha to everyone.\r\n Everyone who dies here becomes immortal Brahmas.\r\n That which is renowned in the 3 Lokas as the city on the bank of the Ganga. 0 \n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nDevi Bhim Chandi Mandir\nSecond stop on the Panch Koshi parikrama.\n\n\n\n\n\nView of the Ganga from Lalita Ghat\nBoats in the Ganga in Varanasi.\n\n\n\n\n\nApproach to Devi Bhim Chandi Mandir\nSecond stop on the Panch Koshi parikrama.\n\n\n\n\n\n\nPrevious\n\n\n\nNext\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nAbout Varanasi\nThe word Varanasi is made up of the two words Varuna and Assi.Varanasi is the city between the rivers Varuna and Assi. It is the holiest city for Hindus. It is the Avimukta Kshetra where Purusha and Prakriti dwelt first. Varanasi is Shiva KShetra. It was a Vishnu KShetra before. \r\n Varanasi is settle next to the left banks of the Ganga and numerous Ghats line up their. Varanasi is also the dwelling place of Shiva where he lives as the Vishweshwar Linga in the Kashi Viswanath Mandir at Gyanvapi.\r\n \n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nThe Assi River\nThe Assi River flows into the Ganga at the famous Assi Ghat. The Assi Ghat is famous as the dwelling place of Goswami Tulsidas ji.\r\n The Ramacharita Manas was composed here. The Assi Ghat is famous for the early morning Kirtans and cultural activities. The Ganga Aarti takes place here.\r\n The Assi River flows next to the Baba Kinarama Asthal. The river has unfortunately been polluted beyond recognition by sewers emptying into it.\r\n Efforts are being made to revive it.\r\n \n\n\n\n\n\n\nPlaces in Varanasi\n\n\n\n\nBheem Chandi\nBheem Chandi,Rameshwar\n\n\n\n\n\nRameshwar Mahadev Mandir on the Varuna\nThird stop on the Panchkoshi parikrama\n\n\n\n\n\nKapil Dhara, Varanasi\nLast stop on the Panchkoshi parikrama Yatra\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nBhairav Nath Mandir.\nOn the Rajatalab to Jansa Road\n\n\n\n\n\nPancha Pandava Mandir, Varanasi\n fourth stop on the Kashi Panchkoshi parikrama.\n\n\n\n\n\nKapil Dhara, Varanasi\nFifth and last stop on the Panchkoshi parikrama\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nMap of Varanasi\n\n\n\n\n\n\n NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN

It is the holiest city for Hindus. It is the Avimukta Kshetra where Purusha and Prakriti dwelt first. Varanasi is Shiva KShetra. It was a Vishnu KShetra before. \r\n Varanasi is settle next to the left banks of the Ganga and numerous Ghats line up their. Varanasi is also the dwelling place of Shiva where he lives as the Vishweshwar Linga in the Kashi Viswanath Mandir at Gyanvapi.\r\n \n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nThe Assi River\nThe Assi River flows into the Ganga at the famous Assi Ghat. The Assi Ghat is famous as the dwelling place of Goswami Tulsidas ji.\r\n The Ramacharita Manas was composed here. The Assi Ghat is famous for the early morning Kirtans and cultural activities. The Ganga Aarti takes place here.\r\n The Assi River flows next to the Baba Kinarama Asthal. The river has unfortunately been polluted beyond recognition by sewers emptying into it.\r\n Efforts are being made to revive it.\r\n \n\n\n\n\n\n\nPlaces in Varanasi\n\n\n\n\nBheem Chandi\nBheem Chandi,Rameshwar\n\n\n\n\n\nRameshwar Mahadev Mandir on the Varuna\nThird stop on the Panchkoshi parikrama\n\n\n\n\n\nKapil Dhara, Varanasi\nLast stop on the Panchkoshi parikrama Yatra\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nBhairav Nath Mandir.\nOn the Rajatalab to Jansa Road\n\n\n\n\n\nPancha Pandava Mandir, Varanasi\n fourth stop on the Kashi Panchkoshi parikrama.\n\n\n\n\n\nKapil Dhara, Varanasi\nFifth and last stop on the Panchkoshi parikrama\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nMap of Varanasi\n\n\n\n\n\n NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN

The Assi Ghat is famous as the dwelling place of Goswami Tulsidas ji.\r\n The Ramacharita Manas was composed here. The Assi Ghat is famous for the early morning Kirtans and cultural activities. 0 \n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nKardameshwar Mandir\nFirst stop on the Panch Koshi parikrama.\n\n\n\n\n\nKardameshwar Mandir Sarovar\nFirst stop on the Panchkoshi parikrama.\n\n\n\n\n\nSeats at the Kardameshwar Mandir\nFirst stop on the Panch Koshi parikrama.\n\n\n\n\n\n\nPrevious\n\n\n\nNext\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nThe Kardameshwar Mandir, Varanasi\nThe Kardameshwar Mandir is the first stop of the Pachkoshi pilgrimage. The oldest surviving Mandir in Varanasi. The Shikhara of this Mandir is the only one that survived the Islamic and British Invasions.\r\nKardameshwar Mahadev is a must visit.\r\n\r\n \nCreation of Rishi Kardam and the other Prajapatis.\n\r\n Rishi Kardam is one of the Prajapatis created by Brahma Ji. Bhrigu, Marichi,\r\nAtri, Daksha, Kardam, Pulastya, Pulaha, Angira and Kratu are some of the Prajapatis.\r\n\r\nRishi Kardam and Dharma were created from the shadow of Bhagwan Brahma.\r\n\r\nBrahma created Rishi Marichi from his eyes, Rishi Bhrigu came from his heart.\r\nRishi Angira came from his head,Rishi Pulaha from his Vyan Vayu and Rishi Pulatsya from his Udana Vaya.\r\n\r\nRishi Vashishtha the Rajguru of Ayodhya came from his Samana Vayu. Rishi Kratu from his Apan Vayu.\r\nAtri Rishi descended from the ear of Brahma.\r\nNarada came from the lap of Brahma. Another Prajapati was Daksha.\r\n\n\nMarriage and children of Rishi Kardam\n\r\n Brahma Ji ordered Rishi Kardam to tapasya and accordingly the Rishi undertook Tapasya.\r\n After this Rishi Kardam was married to Devahuti the daughter of Manu and Shatrupa. Rishi Kardam and Devahuti were the first couple to undertake creation in the earthly way.\r\n The Rishi couple had nine daughters.These were Kala, Anusuya, Shraddha, Havirbhu, Gati, Shanti, Krita,Khyati and Arundhati.\r\n\r\n The daughters were married off. Kala to Marichi,Anusuya to Atri, Shradha to Angira, Havirbhu to Pulasatya, Gati to Pulah, Shanti to Atharva, Krita to Kratu,Khyati to Bhrigu, and Arundhati to Vasistha.\r\n \nShri Kapila Muni the son of Rishi Kardam and Devi Devahuti\n\r\n Shri Vishnu himself took birth as the son of the Rishi couple.Kapila Muni preached Adhyatma Yoga to his mother Mata Devahuti. Kala to Marichi,Anusuya to Atri, Shradha to Angira, Havirbhu to Pulasatya, Gati to Pulah, Shanti to Atharva, Krita to Kratu,Khyati to Bhrigu, and Arundhati to Vasistha.\r\n \nShri Kapila Muni the son of Rishi Kardam and Devi Devahuti\n\r\n Shri Vishnu himself took birth as the son of the Rishi couple.Kapila Muni preached Adhyatma Yoga to his mother Mata Devahuti. Rishi Kardam took sanyas leaving aside the grihastha ashram.\r\n \nRevised on 09-Sep-2019 by Champak Roy\n\n\n\n\n\nKardameshwar Mandir, Mata Mandir\nMata Mandir\n\n\n\n\n\nKardameshwar Mandir,Mata Mandir detail.\nMurti detail\n\n\n\n\n\nKardameshwar Mandir Rudrashtakam, Varanasi\nKardameshwar Mandir. first stop on the Panchkoshi parikrama.\n\n\n\n\n\nKardameshwar Mandir Sarovar, Varanasi\nKardameshwar Mandir Sarovar\n\n\n\n\n\nTo see more images please click here\n\n\n\n\nMap of Shri Kardameshwar Mahadev Mandir area, Varanasi\n\n\n\n\n\n\n NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN

The oldest surviving Mandir in Varanasi. The Shikhara of this Mandir is the only one that survived the Islamic and British Invasions.\r\nKardameshwar Mahadev is a must visit.\r\n\r\n \nCreation of Rishi Kardam and the other Prajapatis.\n\r\n Rishi Kardam is one of the Prajapatis created by Brahma Ji. Bhrigu, Marichi,\r\nAtri, Daksha, Kardam, Pulastya, Pulaha, Angira and Kratu are some of the Prajapatis.\r\n\r\nRishi Kardam and Dharma were created from the shadow of Bhagwan Brahma.\r\n\r\nBrahma created Rishi Marichi from his eyes, Rishi Bhrigu came from his heart.\r\nRishi Angira came from his head,Rishi Pulaha from his Vyan Vayu and Rishi Pulatsya from his Udana Vaya.\r\n\r\nRishi Vashishtha the Rajguru of Ayodhya came from his Samana Vayu. Rishi Kratu from his Apan Vayu.\r\nAtri Rishi descended from the ear of Brahma.\r\nNarada came from the lap of Brahma. Another Prajapati was Daksha.\r\n\n\nMarriage and children of Rishi Kardam\n\r\n Brahma Ji ordered Rishi Kardam to tapasya and accordingly the Rishi undertook Tapasya.\r\n After this Rishi Kardam was married to Devahuti the daughter of Manu and Shatrupa. Rishi Kardam and Devahuti were the first couple to undertake creation in the earthly way.\r\n The Rishi couple had nine daughters.These were Kala, Anusuya, Shraddha, Havirbhu, Gati, Shanti, Krita,Khyati and Arundhati.\r\n\r\n The daughters were married off. Kala to Marichi,Anusuya to Atri, Shradha to Angira, Havirbhu to Pulasatya, Gati to Pulah, Shanti to Atharva, Krita to Kratu,Khyati to Bhrigu, and Arundhati to Vasistha.\r\n \nShri Kapila Muni the son of Rishi Kardam and Devi Devahuti\n\r\n Shri Vishnu himself took birth as the son of the Rishi couple.Kapila Muni preached Adhyatma Yoga to his mother Mata Devahuti. Rishi Kardam took sanyas leaving aside the grihastha ashram.\r\n \nRevised on 09-Sep-2019 by Champak Roy\n\n\n\n\n\nKardameshwar Mandir, Mata Mandir\nMata Mandir\n\n\n\n\n\nKardameshwar Mandir,Mata Mandir detail.\nMurti detail\n\n\n\n\n\nKardameshwar Mandir Rudrashtakam, Varanasi\nKardameshwar Mandir. first stop on the Panchkoshi parikrama.\n\n\n\n\n\nKardameshwar Mandir Sarovar, Varanasi\nKardameshwar Mandir Sarovar\n\n\n\n\n\nTo see more images please click here\n\n\n\n\nMap of Shri Kardameshwar Mahadev Mandir area, Varanasi\n\n\n\n\n\n NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN

The oldest surviving Mandir in Varanasi. The Shikhara of this Mandir is the only one that survived the Islamic and British Invasions.\r\nKardameshwar Mahadev is a must visit.\r\n\r\n \nCreation of Rishi Kardam and the other Prajapatis.\n\r\n Rishi Kardam is one of the Prajapatis created by Brahma Ji. Bhrigu, Marichi,\r\nAtri, Daksha, Kardam, Pulastya, Pulaha, Angira and Kratu are some of the Prajapatis.\r\n\r\nRishi Kardam and Dharma were created from the shadow of Bhagwan Brahma.\r\n\r\nBrahma created Rishi Marichi from his eyes, Rishi Bhrigu came from his heart.\r\nRishi Angira came from his head,Rishi Pulaha from his Vyan Vayu and Rishi Pulatsya from his Udana Vaya.\r\n\r\nRishi Vashishtha the Rajguru of Ayodhya came from his Samana Vayu. Rishi Kratu from his Apan Vayu.\r\nAtri Rishi descended from the ear of Brahma.\r\nNarada came from the lap of Brahma. Another Prajapati was Daksha.\r\n\n\nMarriage and children of Rishi Kardam\n\r\n Brahma Ji ordered Rishi Kardam to tapasya and accordingly the Rishi undertook Tapasya.\r\n After this Rishi Kardam was married to Devahuti the daughter of Manu and Shatrupa. Rishi Kardam and Devahuti were the first couple to undertake creation in the earthly way.\r\n The Rishi couple had nine daughters.These were Kala, Anusuya, Shraddha, Havirbhu, Gati, Shanti, Krita,Khyati and Arundhati.\r\n\r\n The daughters were married off. Kala to Marichi,Anusuya to Atri, Shradha to Angira, Havirbhu to Pulasatya, Gati to Pulah, Shanti to Atharva, Krita to Kratu,Khyati to Bhrigu, and Arundhati to Vasistha.\r\n \nShri Kapila Muni the son of Rishi Kardam and Devi Devahuti\n\r\n Shri Vishnu himself took birth as the son of the Rishi couple.Kapila Muni preached Adhyatma Yoga to his mother Mata Devahuti. Rishi Kardam took sanyas leaving aside the grihastha ashram.\r\n \nRevised on 09-Sep-2019 by Champak Roy\n\n\n\n\n\nKardameshwar Mandir, Mata Mandir\nMata Mandir\n\n\n\n\n\nKardameshwar Mandir,Mata Mandir detail.\nMurti detail\n\n\n\n\n\nKardameshwar Mandir Rudrashtakam, Varanasi\nKardameshwar Mandir. first stop on the Panchkoshi parikrama.\n\n\n\n\n\nKardameshwar Mandir Sarovar, Varanasi\nKardameshwar Mandir Sarovar\n\n\n\n\n\nTo see more images please click here\n\n\n\n\nMap of Shri Kardameshwar Mahadev Mandir area, Varanasi\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nCONTACT\n\n\nContact us for any query about Varanasi and we'll get back to you within 24 hours.\n Varanasi, India\n +91 9335874326\n varanasikshetra@gmail.com\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nSend\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n©Champak's World\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n NaN NaN

0 \n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nThe Gomati Ganga Sangam at Kaithi\nThe place is used for flower farming. Adds beauty and reverence\n\n\n\n\n\nSunrise at Kaithi\nThis is the best time to visit Kaithi or any other Teertha Sthana. Should reach just before dawn.\r\n \r\n .\n\n\n\n\n\nShri Markandeya Mahadev Mandir, Kaithi \nShikhara\n\n\n\n\n\nShri Surya rises over Kaithi\nBest time to reach.\n\n\n\n\n\n\nPrevious\n\n\n\nNext\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nShri Markandeya Mahadev Mandir at Gomati-Ganga Sangam, Kaithi near Varanasi\n\r\nKaithi is situated some 30 kilometers from Varanasi on the Varanasi Ghazipur highway. It is the place where the Gomati joins the Ganga. The \r\nGomati-Ganga Sangam. It is home to the renowned Markandeya Mahadev Mandir.\r\nRishi Markandeya is the author of the Durga Saptashati. His story is told in the Markandeya Purana.\r\n\r\nRishi Markandeya is also one of the renowned guides on Hindu iconography and artistry.\r\n\r\nRishi Markandeya was the son of Rishi Mrikandu and his wife Devi Marudmati.\r\nThe Rishi couple prayed to Shiva for a child. Shiva granted their wish. The couple were offered a choice between an\r\nintelligent son who would die early and a long lived son of low intelligence. The Rishi couple chose the former.\r\n\r\n\r\nAt the age of 16 Yama came for the child who was protected by Shiva as Kalantaka.\r\n\n\r\n\r\n\r\n You do not actually visit a Mandir or any other Teertha Sthana of your own accord. You reach there when the presiding Ishwara actually calls you.\r\n \r\n I learned this while attempting a visit to Kaithi. I had been planning a visit since a minimum 3 years but it wouldn't fructify.\r\n I got aboard a vehicle once and then had to come down because some guests arrived.\r\n \r\n Shiva had planned something else. I happened to make friendship with a local man from Kaithi who picked me up on his vehicle at 3:30 AM from Varanasi and we reached Kaithi just about 10 minutes before sunrise.\r\n Revised on 16-Oct-2019 by Champak Roy\n\n\n\n\n\nBells at Shri Markandeya Mahadev Mandir, Kaithi\n\n\n\n\n\n\nInside Shri Markandeya Mahadev Mandir, Kaithi\n\n\n\n\n\n\nInside Shri Markandeya Mahadev Mandir, Kaithi\n\n\n\n\n\n\nShikhara of Shri Markandeya Mahadev, Kaithi\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nSunrise at Kaithi, Markandeya Mahadev\n\n\n\n\n\n\nSunrise at Kaithi, Markandeya Mahadev\n\n\n\n\n\n\nSunrise at Kaithi, Markandeya Mahadev\n\n\n\n\n\n\nSunrise at Kaithi, Markandeya Mahadev\n\n\n\n\n\n\nTo see more images please click here\n\n\n\n\nMap of Shri Markandeya Mahadev, Gomati-Ganga Sangam, Varanasi\n\n\n\n\n\n\n NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN

2 NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN \n\nHome\n\nKashi Panchkoshi Parikrama \n\nKashi Panchkoshi Parikrama\nKardameshwar Mahadev\nBheem Chandi\nRameshwar Mahadev\nPanch Pandava\nKapil Dhara\n\n\n\nGalleries \n\nKardameshwar Mahadev\nBheem Chandi Gallery\nRameshwar Gallery\nKapil Dhara\n\n\n\nMandirs \n\nShri Adi Keshava Mandir\nMarkandeya Mahadev,Kaithi\nBhairav Nath Mandir\nDindaspur, Harsos, Jansa\nPahadia Mandir, Akhara and Sarovar\n\n\n\nGhats\nFestivals\n\n\n NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN
3 NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN \n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nThe Gomati Ganga Sangam at Kaithi\nThe place is used for flower farming. Adds beauty and reverence\n\n\n\n\n\nSunrise at Kaithi\nThis is the best time to visit Kaithi or any other Teertha Sthana. Should reach just before dawn.\r\n \r\n .\n\n\n\n\n\nShri Markandeya Mahadev Mandir, Kaithi \nShikhara\n\n\n\n\n\nShri Surya rises over Kaithi\nBest time to reach.\n\n\n\n\n\n\nPrevious\n\n\n\nNext\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nShri Markandeya Mahadev Mandir at Gomati-Ganga Sangam, Kaithi near Varanasi\n\r\nKaithi is situated some 30 kilometers from Varanasi on the Varanasi Ghazipur highway. It is the place where the Gomati joins the Ganga. The \r\nGomati-Ganga Sangam. It is home to the renowned Markandeya Mahadev Mandir.\r\nRishi Markandeya is the author of the Durga Saptashati. His story is told in the Markandeya Purana.\r\n\r\nRishi Markandeya is also one of the renowned guides on Hindu iconography and artistry.\r\n\r\nRishi Markandeya was the son of Rishi Mrikandu and his wife Devi Marudmati.\r\nThe Rishi couple prayed to Shiva for a child. Shiva granted their wish. The couple were offered a choice between an\r\nintelligent son who would die early and a long lived son of low intelligence. The Rishi couple chose the former.\r\n\r\n\r\nAt the age of 16 Yama came for the child who was protected by Shiva as Kalantaka.\r\n\n\r\n\r\n\r\n You do not actually visit a Mandir or any other Teertha Sthana of your own accord. You reach there when the presiding Ishwara actually calls you.\r\n \r\n I learned this while attempting a visit to Kaithi. I had been planning a visit since a minimum 3 years but it wouldn't fructify.\r\n I got aboard a vehicle once and then had to come down because some guests arrived.\r\n \r\n Shiva had planned something else. I happened to make friendship with a local man from Kaithi who picked me up on his vehicle at 3:30 AM from Varanasi and we reached Kaithi just about 10 minutes before sunrise.\r\n Revised on 16-Oct-2019 by Champak Roy\n\n\n\n\n\nBells at Shri Markandeya Mahadev Mandir, Kaithi\n\n\n\n\n\n\nInside Shri Markandeya Mahadev Mandir, Kaithi\n\n\n\n\n\n\nInside Shri Markandeya Mahadev Mandir, Kaithi\n\n\n\n\n\n\nShikhara of Shri Markandeya Mahadev, Kaithi\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nSunrise at Kaithi, Markandeya Mahadev\n\n\n\n\n\n\nSunrise at Kaithi, Markandeya Mahadev\n\n\n\n\n\n\nSunrise at Kaithi, Markandeya Mahadev\n\n\n\n\n\n\nSunrise at Kaithi, Markandeya Mahadev\n\n\n\n\n\n\nTo see more images please click here\n\n\n\n\nMap of Shri Markandeya Mahadev, Gomati-Ganga Sangam, Varanasi\n\n\n\n\n\n NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN

It is the place where the Gomati joins the Ganga. The \r\nGomati-Ganga Sangam. It is home to the renowned Markandeya Mahadev Mandir.\r\nRishi Markandeya is the author of the Durga Saptashati. It is the place where the Gomati joins the Ganga. The \r\nGomati-Ganga Sangam. It is home to the renowned Markandeya Mahadev Mandir.\r\nRishi Markandeya is the author of the Durga Saptashati. His story is told in the Markandeya Purana.\r\n\r\nRishi Markandeya is also one of the renowned guides on Hindu iconography and artistry.\r\n\r\nRishi Markandeya was the son of Rishi Mrikandu and his wife Devi Marudmati.\r\nThe Rishi couple prayed to Shiva for a child. Shiva granted their wish. The couple were offered a choice between an\r\nintelligent son who would die early and a long lived son of low intelligence. The Rishi couple chose the former.\r\n\r\n\r\nAt the age of 16 Yama came for the child who was protected by Shiva as Kalantaka.\r\n\n\r\n\r\n\r\n You do not actually visit a Mandir or any other Teertha Sthana of your own accord. You reach there when the presiding Ishwara actually calls you.\r\n \r\n I learned this while attempting a visit to Kaithi. I had been planning a visit since a minimum 3 years but it wouldn't fructify.\r\n I got aboard a vehicle once and then had to come down because some guests arrived.\r\n \r\n Shiva had planned something else. I happened to make friendship with a local man from Kaithi who picked me up on his vehicle at 3:30 AM from Varanasi and we reached Kaithi just about 10 minutes before sunrise.\r\n Revised on 16-Oct-2019 by Champak Roy\n\n\n\n\n\nBells at Shri Markandeya Mahadev Mandir, Kaithi\n\n\n\n\n\n\nInside Shri Markandeya Mahadev Mandir, Kaithi\n\n\n\n\n\n\nInside Shri Markandeya Mahadev Mandir, Kaithi\n\n\n\n\n\n\nShikhara of Shri Markandeya Mahadev, Kaithi\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nSunrise at Kaithi, Markandeya Mahadev\n\n\n\n\n\n\nSunrise at Kaithi, Markandeya Mahadev\n\n\n\n\n\n\nSunrise at Kaithi, Markandeya Mahadev\n\n\n\n\n\n\nSunrise at Kaithi, Markandeya Mahadev\n\n\n\n\n\n\nTo see more images please click here\n\n\n\n\nMap of Shri Markandeya Mahadev, Gomati-Ganga Sangam, Varanasi\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nCONTACT\n\n\nContact us for any query about Varanasi and we'll get back to you within 24 hours.\n Varanasi, India\n +91 9335874326\n varanasikshetra@gmail.com\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nSend\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n©Champak's World\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN
